{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH7PmxGF8bJ5z1xfrXij","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. Both tests pass.\n\n**The bug** (`src/money.js`): the discount was applied and rounded on **each line separately**, then the rounded per-line amounts were summed. The spec (and the docstring) says the discount applies to the **order subtotal** and should be **rounded once**.\n\nRounding per line means each line's fractional cent rounds independently, so several lines can each round up and inflate the total. In the reported case — two $4.50 lines with a small discount — each line rounded up to $4.50, summing to $9.00, when the subtotal-once calculation gives $8.99.\n\n**The fix:** sum the exact integer subtotal first, apply the discount, and round the final result a single time. I also added a regression test capturing the exact $9.00-vs-$8.99 scenario. (I left `report.js`'s `.toFixed(2)` alone — cents are already integers there, so it's fine despite the \"sketchy?\" TODO.)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":305,"cache_read_input_tokens":25441,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":305},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"19ed419d-c011-46f0-a1a0-70183120578e","uuid":"51857b13-4bdc-44dd-aa43-668de272fef2","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:39:55.951Z","request_id":"req_011CdH7Pkaf7oksmHJ31t2Lp"}
